The angles $\angle APF$ and $\angle BPF$ are equal if and only if the slopes of $\overline{AP}$ and $\overline{BP}$ are equal.

The slope of $\overline{AP}$ is $\frac{\sin t - 0}{\sqrt{2}p\cos t - 1}$ and the slope of $\overline{BP}$ is $\frac{\sin(t + \theta) - \sin t}{\sqrt{2}p\cos(t + \theta) - \sqrt{2}\cos t}$.

