\end{align*}

Since the radius of the circle is equal to the distance between $(2,4)$ and the center of the circle, we have

\begin{align*}
r^2&=(2-h)^2+(4-k)^2,\\
(h^2-4h+5)&=(2-h)^2+(4-k)^2.
\end{align*}

Expanding and simplifying, we have

